<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-02-13T06:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-02-13T06:00:00-05:00" n="7" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d7">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">121.840 Welles, Sumner/25: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Italy</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Phillips</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Rome</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-02-13T12:00:00+01:00">February
                                    13, 1940—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received February 13—9
                                a.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>101. Department’s 32, February 12, 1 p.m. For Welles. I conveyed to Count
                            Ciano this morning your appreciation of his message and he assured me
                            that he and the Chief of the Government will be glad to receive you
                            immediately after your arrival, presumably on the 26th.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Phillips</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>